summary:
KILLING EVE SEASON 2 EPISODE 6.
Ok, i don’t think there’s a look that doesn’t suit Villanelle. But honestly, i think her arc is...
body:
KILLING EVE SEASON 2 EPISODE 6.


Ok, i don’t think there’s a look that doesn’t suit Villanelle. But honestly, i think her arc is about to get the most darkest and most dangerous yet. I think she’s gonna come close to coming unstuck with being undercover.

The amount of danger she’s about to put herself in is what i think will really test Eve in what way Villanelle actually means to her. Because at the moment, i think Eves doing a very good job infront of Villanelle of making her seem like she doesn’t care; and i think Villanelle will start to believe it.

Upcoming episodes summaries state Eve is fighting for her affection? after episode 5, something must happen to make Eve click into this feeling because she done a very good job infront of Villanelle in elisode 5 of hiding it at moments. Others; not so well.

I mean Villanelle has confronted Nico now? I honestly don’t think this is gonna go down well. Unless it does the opposite of showing Eve that someone will actually fight for her?

summary:
Please let's stop infantilizing Villanelle and stop villainizing Eve. 
Stop acting like Eve has no reason to have her walls up...
body:
Please let’s stop infantilizing Villanelle and stop villainizing Eve.

Stop acting like Eve has no reason to have her walls up just as Villanelle has hers to do the same and stop saying what a bitch Eve as if Villanelle wasn’t just the same as her.

That’s the point guys. How these two women are meeting in the middle and becoming like each other.

Just cause we’ve seen Villanelle showing real emotions doesn’t mean Eve knows V wants something real after what Konstantin said, after that psychopaths presentation, and especially after we see how Villanelle is still trying to play mind games with her. We’ve also seen the undoubtedly longing and obsession Eve has towards V.

Neither is being truthful to each other. Eve is not being truthful to herself. Both are still enjoying to fuck the other up. And it’s sexy. And it’s part of the journey.

Really, what were you expecting? They’d fall into each other arms and confess the depth of their feelings to each other and kiss with the setting sun as the background?

Even when they do reach mutual understanding, it wouldnt be smart to think they won’t keep hurting each other. Just remember how toxic this ship can and will become. The producers said so, the actresses said so, common sense says so.

summary: I’m not really in the Killing Eve fandom, I just watch the show, so here is my one contribution to meta and analysis of the...
body:
I’m not really in the Killing Eve fandom, I just watch the show, so here is my one contribution to meta and analysis of the show: 

When Eve goes to talk to The Ghost at the end of 2x04, she puts her hair up. 

In season 1, Villanelle tells her to wear her hair down, and she listens - she keeps wearing it down a lot more throughout the two seasons. 

Do with that observation what you will
